column3:
Nino Ba\v{s}i\'c, Sarah Berkemer, J\"org Fallmann, Patrick W. Fowler,
  Thomas Gatter, Toma\v{z} Pisanski, Nancy Retzlaff, Peter F. Stadler, Sara S.
  Zemlji\v{c}

column5:
15 pages, 9 figures: V2: slight change in title and abstract;
  significant discussion and references added; conceptual changes; now 19
  pages. Matches published version

column11:
  In this paper, we prove a congruence which confirms a conjecture of Adamchuk.
For any prime $p\equiv1\pmod3$ and $a\in\mathbb{Z}^{+}$, we have \begin{align*}
\sum_{k=1}^{\frac{2}3(p^a-1)}\binom{2k}k\equiv0\pmod{p^2}. \end{align*}
